                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Text is on both sides, 6 lines on Side 1 (Recto) and 6 lines on Side 2 (Verso).  While the script contains some features of the oldest types, it looks decidedly younger. Diacritical signs are expressed by strokes and vowels marked by dots, originally red, now black because of oxidation. (S.L. Skoss?)</note>
                     <note type="local_note">Museum of Archaeology and Anthropology, Ellen W. Harrison Collection</note>
